This comes after the power utility announced it would implement stage 1 load shedding  Thursday morning JOHANNESBURG -  Eskom has announced that it will be implementing stage 2 load shedding from 3 pm until 11 pm on Thursday. On Thursday morning, the power utility announced it will be implementing stage 1 load shedding due to plant breakdowns  resulting in an imbalance between supply and demand.    City Power has had to revise its load shedding schedule. Spokesperson Isaac Mangena said: “We appeal to residents to basically ensure that they are prepared for this stage 2.”